title: Jay Inslee
added: On April 8, 2021, Inslee signed a bill restoring voting rights to convicted felons after they finish serving their sentences. This made Washington the 20th state to have such laws, and it was primarily sponsored by representative [[Tarra Simmons]], who was formerly incarcerated herself.<ref>{{cite news|title=Inslee signs bill restoring voting rights to parolees in Washington state|url=https://thehill.com/homenews/state-watch/547142-inslee-signs-bill-restoring-voting-rights-to-parolees-in-washington?amp|newspaper=[[The Hill (newspaper)|The Hill]]|date=April 8, 2021}}</ref>

title: Jay Inslee
deleted: In October of 2021 Inslee dictated that all state employees must get vaccinated from the Corona Virus by October 18th. Many employees showed resistance to the vaccine mandate. Multiple highway patrol officers resigned after serverving 10-20 years stating that they would not get a vaccine because of moral reason. They stated they had a right to what they put in their bodies and the right to their own healthcare.
